comments.body:
Ran into the same problem today, resolved it with the proposed method in the [thread](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/issues/2006#issue-1168544195) you mentioned, ie. prepending formula string with `_xlfn.`.

Original code: 
```
cell.value = {
          formula: `IFNA(VLOOKUP(${toExcelColumnName(colNumber - 1)}${rowNumber}, ${doctorsSheet.name}!A1:B${doctors.length + 1}, 2, FALSE), "")`,
        }
```

Solution:
```
cell.value = {
          formula: `_xlfn.IFNA(VLOOKUP(${toExcelColumnName(colNumber - 1)}${rowNumber}, ${doctorsSheet.name}!A1:B${doctors.length + 1}, 2, FALSE), "")`,
        }
```

@Javadebi Have you tried only prepending to the start of the string instead of every single Excel function?
